1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:05,964
<i>We can see two hostages now</i>
<i>on the top floor of St. John's Hospital.</i>

2
00:00:06,047 --> 00:00:08,717
<i>It looks like the hostage takers</i>
<i>are planning to push them.</i>

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:09,676
<i>Padua!</i>

4
00:00:09,759 --> 00:00:11,386
<i>There are no cops inside anymore.</i>

5
00:00:11,469 --> 00:00:13,221
<i>I give you my word.</i>

6
00:00:13,304 --> 00:00:14,389
<i>Let them go.</i>

7
00:00:14,973 --> 00:00:16,099
<i>Well, Magnus Roja?</i>

8
00:00:16,182 --> 00:00:21,980
<i>Which of your two sons</i>
<i>are you going to choose to save,</i>

9
00:00:22,063 --> 00:00:24,941
<i>and which one will you leave to die?</i>

10
00:00:25,024 --> 00:00:26,609
<i>Why are you hesitating?</i>

11
00:00:26,693 --> 00:00:30,071
<i>Wendy said it herself!</i>
<i>Olsen is not your son.</i>

12
00:00:30,155 --> 00:00:32,824
<i>- Don't listen to her.</i>
<i>- Magnus, Olsen's your son.</i>

13
00:00:32,907 --> 00:00:34,701
<i>Olsen, son.</i>

14
00:00:34,784 --> 00:00:37,245
<i>Only one of them can live.</i>

15
00:00:37,328 --> 00:00:38,788
<i>So make your choice.</i>

16
00:00:38,872 --> 00:00:41,207
- [MAGNUS] <i>I'm sorry, Olsen.</i>
- [WENDY] <i>No!</i>

17
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:43,668
<i>Don't worry,</i>
<i>I won't kill either of them yet.</i>

18
00:00:43,752 --> 00:00:45,545
<i>I can still use them.</i>

19
00:00:45,628 --> 00:00:46,588
[CRYING]

20
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:49,048
[LAUGHING]

21
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:53,762
<i>I only said you were Magnus's son</i>
<i>because I thought he might--</i>

22
00:00:53,845 --> 00:00:56,056
<i>He might choose me.</i>

23
00:00:56,139 --> 00:00:57,223
<i>It's not true?</i>

24
00:00:57,307 --> 00:00:58,975
<i>Olsen's not your son.</i>

25
00:00:59,517 --> 00:01:01,144
<i>So, Olsen's not my brother?</i>

26
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:02,353
<i>I'm sorry, son.</i>

27
00:01:02,437 --> 00:01:05,940
<i>You know, honestly, Pa,</i>
<i>I understand Aunt Wendy.</i>

28
00:01:06,608 --> 00:01:08,318
<i>I get why she did it.</i>

29
00:01:11,154 --> 00:01:13,114
[EMIL] <i>You sly bastard.</i>

30
00:01:13,698 --> 00:01:15,617
<i>You wanted to kill me?</i>

31
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:18,244
<i>Why don't we just pick him to make</i>
<i>an example of for the cops downstairs?</i>

32
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:19,871
<i>He's useless to us anyway.</i>

33
00:01:19,954 --> 00:01:22,165
<i>I know where the loot is.</i>

34
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:23,958
<i>If you kill me,</i>

35
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:27,086
<i>you'll never be able to find</i>
<i>the cash or the jewelry.</i>

36
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:30,590
[EMIL] <i>I'll definitely kill you</i>
<i>if you don't tell us where they are.</i>

37
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:36,387
Where did you hide the loot?

38
00:01:36,471 --> 00:01:41,976
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:44,854
<i>Where's the money?</i>

40
00:01:46,105 --> 00:01:47,315
<i>They have it.</i>

41
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:49,150
<i>How much do they have?</i>

42
00:01:49,234 --> 00:01:53,780
<i>Adding up all they got,</i>
<i>including cash and jewelry,</i>

43
00:01:54,614 --> 00:01:55,990
<i>it's about 300 million.</i>

44
00:01:57,242 --> 00:01:59,077
<i>Do you know where they're keeping it?</i>

45
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:01,204
<i>Why?</i>

46
00:02:01,287 --> 00:02:03,581
<i>I need you to do one more thing.</i>

47
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,964
Where did you hide the money?

48
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:13,800
- Where?!
- Wait!

49
00:02:13,883 --> 00:02:14,843
[GRUNTS]

50
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:17,137
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,013
It's…

52
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:20,598
It's on the island.

53
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:23,518
Where exactly?

54
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:25,520
At…

55
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:27,981
At the staff house.

56
00:02:29,691 --> 00:02:33,194
Inside-- Inside a room that was
turned into a storage area.

57
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:36,990
The jewelry and money are safe there.
No one will see them.

58
00:02:37,073 --> 00:02:40,076
I even piled stuff on top to cover them.

59
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:42,370
[DADO] Boss.

60
00:02:43,037 --> 00:02:44,497
Do you know where that is?

61
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:46,833
Yes.

62
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:50,753
There are only two staff houses
at the resort.

63
00:02:53,256 --> 00:02:55,884
- I'll get them for you.
- [DADO SCOFFS]

64
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:57,802
[JACINTO] I'll go back to La Playa Roja.

65
00:02:59,137 --> 00:03:01,139
You're easy to talk to.

66
00:03:01,222 --> 00:03:04,225
And because of that, you're off the hook.

67
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:07,854
[EMIL] I might even increase your share.

68
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:11,357
After all, if it weren't for you,

69
00:03:12,066 --> 00:03:17,238
there wouldn't have been
a hostage taking at La Playa Roja.

70
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:19,991
Yes.

71
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:23,745
He's the mastermind.

72
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:28,041
The real boss of all of us.

73
00:03:28,124 --> 00:03:28,958
It's not me.

74
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:32,587
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

75
00:03:32,670 --> 00:03:34,923
<i>I have two conditions.</i>

76
00:03:36,174 --> 00:03:42,263
<i>One. No one must know that I'm involved.</i>

77
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:47,018
<i>And two, no one gets hurt</i>

78
00:03:48,937 --> 00:03:51,397
<i>while you're doing the hostage taking.</i>

79
00:03:52,357 --> 00:03:54,400
<i>Especially not my family.</i>

80
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:56,527
<i>Do you understand?</i>

81
00:03:59,489 --> 00:04:00,573
<i>It's settled.</i>

82
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:04,661
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

83
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:05,745
Let's go.

84
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:09,707
- Come on! Grab him.
- Wait. Wait!

85
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:12,335
[JACINTO] Wait! Wa--

86
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:15,338
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

87
00:04:15,421 --> 00:04:18,299
- [MAN 1] Who is that?
- [MAN 2] Look!

88
00:04:18,383 --> 00:04:20,551
- [MAN 1] They're pushing him!
- [MAN 3] My goodness!

89
00:04:20,635 --> 00:04:21,970
[JACINTO SCREAMING]

90
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:26,099
- [BODY THUDS]
- [GRETA GASPS]

91
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:28,393
[SINISTER LAUGHTER]

92
00:04:37,318 --> 00:04:44,284
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

93
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:16,441
- [MAN] Help him!
- Medic!

94
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:18,735
Hurry!

95
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:25,325
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

96
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:45,803
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

97
00:05:57,231 --> 00:06:03,738
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

98
00:06:03,821 --> 00:06:06,240
[SIREN WAILING]

99
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:10,536
There. The cops can't say
we didn't keep our word.

100
00:06:14,082 --> 00:06:16,292
The bastard fell straight to hell.

101
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:20,838
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

102
00:06:20,922 --> 00:06:22,215
Well?

103
00:06:22,298 --> 00:06:23,382
Case closed.

104
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:26,344
We know where the millions are now.

105
00:06:26,427 --> 00:06:28,971
And our cut just got bigger.

106
00:06:30,973 --> 00:06:35,686
Jacinto's share was huge, 30 percent.

107
00:06:36,896 --> 00:06:40,191
Boss, let's head back to the island.

108
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:44,445
Not us.

109
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:50,326
We still need to be sure.

110
00:06:55,164 --> 00:07:02,046
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

111
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:06,801
We'll send them to La Playa Roja.

112
00:07:06,884 --> 00:07:10,471
[MEN LAUGH SINISTERLY]

113
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:19,897
You know the place
Jacinto mentioned, right?

114
00:07:22,859 --> 00:07:24,485
The staff house.

115
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:31,242
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:07:43,254 --> 00:07:44,755
[SOFT TAPPING]

117
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:50,845
[GASPS]

118
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:55,057
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

119
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:56,225
What happened?

120
00:07:56,893 --> 00:07:59,020
- The doctor got away from you.
- [GROANS]

121
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:00,271
He was with a woman.

122
00:08:00,354 --> 00:08:01,981
I think you shot her.

123
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:04,442
Did they get Leni's medicine?

124
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:11,949
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

125
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:15,536
I want to talk to Papa.

126
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:20,041
Why?

127
00:08:21,542 --> 00:08:23,294
You're going to stop him again?

128
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:27,590
Don't waste your time, Leni.

129
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:30,968
What you need to do now is recover.

130
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:34,639
We need to find you a doctor.

131
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:35,932
[LENI COUGHS]

132
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:36,849
No.

133
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:39,519
I don't need a doctor or medicine.

134
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:42,855
I need to get out of here.

135
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:49,320
- Fine. Where do you think you're going?
- [LENI COUGHS]

136
00:08:49,403 --> 00:08:51,864
The moment you step outside,
you're going straight to jail.

137
00:08:53,449 --> 00:08:55,284
There's no turning back from this, Leni.

138
00:08:55,952 --> 00:08:57,745
The money we're getting from this,

139
00:08:57,828 --> 00:08:59,830
that's our only way out.

140
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:03,084
So can you please just cooperate?

141
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,294
Cooperate with what?

142
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:06,796
With killing people?

143
00:09:08,381 --> 00:09:10,258
What did you expect?

144
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:12,593
[EXHALES] That wasn't the plan.

145
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:16,597
I only agreed because--
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

146
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:18,140
Because of the money.

147
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:20,434
For my sister, Ayen.

148
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:23,312
Not to let you go on a massacre.

149
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:25,189
[COUGHS]

150
00:09:25,273 --> 00:09:29,986
How many more lives have to be lost
before you get what you want?

151
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:34,240
Why do you even care about
the people who died?

152
00:09:34,323 --> 00:09:36,909
What matters is that you're alive.

153
00:09:36,993 --> 00:09:40,454
Your father did everything he could
to protect you.

154
00:09:42,373 --> 00:09:44,959
Do you think any of this is easy for us?

155
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:47,837
We're risking our lives too, for--

156
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,755
- For me?
- Yes.

157
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:51,757
For you.

158
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:55,177
For your father. Boss Emil.

159
00:09:56,554 --> 00:09:57,763
Why?

160
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:02,393
Why am I loyal to this group?

161
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:06,897
This is the only place
where I felt like I had a family.

162
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:10,943
My own parents, my own father,

163
00:10:11,027 --> 00:10:13,112
abandoned me when I was a kid.

164
00:10:13,195 --> 00:10:16,282
And even if your father is an asshole,

165
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:19,368
no one else ever made me feel
like I mattered

166
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:23,205
except him and the people around him.

167
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:26,459
So once I get my millions,

168
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:29,879
I'll finally be important too

169
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:31,672
to everyone.

170
00:10:31,756 --> 00:10:35,760
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:10:35,843 --> 00:10:41,182
If you won't help me talk to Papa…

172
00:10:41,265 --> 00:10:42,558
- [GRUNTS SLIGHTLY]
- [GWEN] Leni.

173
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:44,602
- …I'll go to him myself.
- Leni.

174
00:10:44,685 --> 00:10:45,853
Leni, stop.

175
00:10:45,936 --> 00:10:47,730
- [LENI GRUNTS]
- Stop it. Enough.

176
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:50,399
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

177
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:52,526
That's enough.

178
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:53,986
[COUGHS]

179
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:55,029
Ouch.

180
00:10:55,112 --> 00:10:56,530
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

181
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:59,367
I want to talk to Papa. [COUGHS]

182
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:00,493
That's enough.

183
00:11:01,243 --> 00:11:03,287
You take care of her for now.

184
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:07,625
[DOOR CLICKS]

185
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:08,709
[DOOR CLOSES]

186
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:11,962
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

187
00:11:24,892 --> 00:11:31,690
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

188
00:11:42,076 --> 00:11:49,083
[OMINOUS MUSIC SWELLS]

189
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:08,936
[MUSIC SLOWLY FADES]

190
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:14,483
[BANGS ON DOOR]

191
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,654
[GWEN] I know you're in there.

192
00:12:18,737 --> 00:12:22,741
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

193
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:24,201
[GUNSHOTS]

194
00:12:32,877 --> 00:12:34,545
Come with me.

195
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:41,760
No.

196
00:12:43,053 --> 00:12:45,848
If you shoot her, I won't help you.

197
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:52,354
You'll help me,

198
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:54,440
whether you like it or not.

199
00:12:55,858 --> 00:12:57,443
[IVAN] Okay.

200
00:12:59,528 --> 00:13:02,448
[IVAN] But please, don't kill her.

201
00:13:03,073 --> 00:13:04,366
She's too weak.

202
00:13:06,911 --> 00:13:07,828
Besides,

203
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:12,416
if she survives,
she won't be able to do much.

204
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:29,099
- [DARK MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BEEPING]

205
00:13:36,273 --> 00:13:38,692
The task is simple.

206
00:13:40,194 --> 00:13:44,657
Get our money and jewelry from the island.

207
00:13:45,407 --> 00:13:48,619
If you don't return by 12 noon,

208
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:52,873
we'll kill all of them.

209
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:57,336
If you return

210
00:13:57,419 --> 00:14:00,839
without our cash and jewelry…

211
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:09,431
we'll kill you two…

212
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,728
and them afterwards.

213
00:14:18,148 --> 00:14:20,568
So don't get smart with me.

214
00:14:20,651 --> 00:14:24,530
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

215
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:28,659
We've prepared a car
for you to get to the port,

216
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:32,288
and a boat for you to get to the island.

217
00:14:35,207 --> 00:14:37,960
Don't mind the cops.

218
00:14:38,919 --> 00:14:41,422
I've talked to General Cabral.

219
00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:43,340
If someone tries to interfere with you…

220
00:14:45,509 --> 00:14:47,511
I'll show them what I'm capable of again.

221
00:14:51,849 --> 00:14:54,560
The signal jammers on the island
have been removed,

222
00:14:55,269 --> 00:14:57,396
so you can talk to me through this.

223
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:07,197
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:15,789
Be careful, son.

225
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:24,506
Don't abandon us.

226
00:15:27,676 --> 00:15:29,803
We won't, Senator.

227
00:15:31,055 --> 00:15:33,682
Our parents are in here.

228
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,813
We will come back.

229
00:15:43,525 --> 00:15:44,735
As you should.

230
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:51,367
I'll say it again.

231
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:59,667
If you don't return
with our cash and jewelry,

232
00:16:01,251 --> 00:16:03,253
I'll kill them all.

233
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:09,802
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:16:14,765 --> 00:16:17,309
Then, I'll hunt you down.

235
00:16:21,939 --> 00:16:23,691
- Go on.
- Yes, sir.

236
00:16:24,316 --> 00:16:25,651
Move.

237
00:16:25,734 --> 00:16:27,611
Come on. Move it.

238
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:45,838
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

239
00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:52,761
Let's go. Hurry up.

240
00:16:56,265 --> 00:16:57,683
That's your car service.

241
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:18,328
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:20,330
I hope Luna got out safely.

243
00:17:21,498 --> 00:17:22,791
As well as Ice.

244
00:17:24,835 --> 00:17:26,920
Hey, kiddos!

245
00:17:30,466 --> 00:17:31,842
You should be back by 12 o'clock.

246
00:17:32,551 --> 00:17:33,677
You'd better get going.

247
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:40,184
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

248
00:17:40,267 --> 00:17:41,393
Let's go.

249
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:52,237
[AMBULANCE SIREN BLARING]

250
00:18:01,455 --> 00:18:07,002
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

251
00:18:24,353 --> 00:18:26,021
They're here! Come on!

252
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:33,320
- [CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

253
00:18:36,615 --> 00:18:37,616
[GRUNTS]

254
00:18:41,954 --> 00:18:47,709
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

255
00:18:50,045 --> 00:18:52,631
- [REPORTER 1] Sir, wait!
- [REPORTER 2] Quick question!

256
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:06,353
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:13,235
[GRUNTING]

258
00:19:15,612 --> 00:19:16,655
Have you untied it?

259
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:18,323
Yeah, wait a sec.

260
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:20,200
Start the engine.

261
00:19:21,285 --> 00:19:23,162
[ENGINE STARTS]

262
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:36,216
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

263
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:50,814
[OLSEN] <i>We will do what Emil Padua wants.</i>

264
00:19:50,898 --> 00:19:52,357
<i>We'll bring back his money.</i>

265
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:56,612
<i>We'll find a way to save them.</i>
<i>Just like brothers.</i>

266
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:01,074
[EMIL] <i>Find our money.</i>

267
00:20:01,158 --> 00:20:03,327
<i>Turn the island over if you have to.</i>

268
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:05,495
<i>What you're asking from them</i>
<i>is very difficult.</i>

269
00:20:06,288 --> 00:20:08,373
[AREZA] <i>I'm trained for bomb disposal.</i>

270
00:20:08,457 --> 00:20:09,750
<i>I know I can be of use.</i>

271
00:20:09,833 --> 00:20:12,252
<i>You ruined our lives.</i>

272
00:20:13,253 --> 00:20:16,715
<i>I think I might know where they hid</i>
<i>what you're looking for.</i>

273
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:18,175
<i>How do you know?</i>

274
00:20:18,258 --> 00:20:20,385
<i>You shouldn't have attempted</i>
<i>to get her out.</i>

275
00:20:20,469 --> 00:20:21,929
<i>You put her in even more danger.</i>

276
00:20:22,012 --> 00:20:24,431
<i>Just do what you need to do.</i>

277
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:26,934
<i>I'll leave you here for a bit, okay, Pa?</i>

278
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:28,268
<i>- I didn't find--</i>
<i>- Liam!</i>

279
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:31,355
<i>Olsen is not your son!</i>

280
00:20:32,397 --> 00:20:33,232
<i>Wendy?</i>

281
00:20:33,315 --> 00:20:36,276
[LUCAS] <i>Is she the woman you said</i>
<i>you used to live with?</i>

282
00:20:37,110 --> 00:20:39,655
<i>Why was Papa's urn filled with sand?</i>

283
00:20:39,738 --> 00:20:41,907
<i>If we don't succeed,</i>
<i>we'll be the ones turning to dust.</i>

284
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:43,617
<i>- Son?</i>
<i>- Ma?</i>

285
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:46,828
<i>Go to the cottage by the old docks.</i>

286
00:20:46,912 --> 00:20:48,205
<i>There's a loft there.</i>

287
00:20:48,789 --> 00:20:49,915
<i>You know where the money is?</i>

288
00:20:49,998 --> 00:20:52,376
<i>You don't have much time.</i>
<i>Just listen to me.</i>

289
00:20:52,459 --> 00:20:54,044
<i>How did you know?</i>

290
00:20:54,127 --> 00:20:56,380
<i>When Jacinto and I were planning this,</i>

291
00:20:56,463 --> 00:20:59,675
<i>we agreed to just scare the hostages.</i>

292
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:02,844
<i>He said we shouldn't hurt anybody.</i>
<i>Except for one person.</i>

293
00:21:02,928 --> 00:21:04,554
<i>Aside from me?</i>

294
00:21:05,847 --> 00:21:07,975
[EMIL] <i>You know that</i>
<i>I get impatient easily.</i>

295
00:21:08,058 --> 00:21:10,852
<i>We can't waste time here.</i>

296
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:13,397
<i>- What's that?</i>
- [GRUNTS]

297
00:21:14,022 --> 00:21:15,440
<i>Relax.</i>

298
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:17,526
[FIN] <i>No! Don't!</i>

299
00:21:17,609 --> 00:21:18,485
[BEEPS]

300
00:21:18,568 --> 00:21:21,863
- [EXPLOSION]
- [SCREAMING]
